'''Kroppedal''' Museum in Denmark, {{convert|20|km|mi|abbr=on}} from [[Copenhagen]], was established in 2003. Kroppedal is the national museum of Danish astronomy, has a large archaeological unit, and an ethnological unit specializing in modern society. The museum has a permanent exhibition centred on the famous astromer and engineer [[Ole Rømer]] (1644-1710), and its collections include his only surviving pendulum clock.

